dct_description_sm: New Jersey Department of Conservation and Economic Development. Bureau of Geology and Topography. Atlas Sheet 29 (1972) New Jersey Geological Survey. Alternate title: [New Jersey.] Atlas sheet no. 29. Relief shown by 10 ft. contour interval and spot heights. Depth of water shown by soundings in feet at mean low tide. Title is not given. Region covered: Monmouth Shore. Original survey made under direction of C. C. Vermeule, Topographer in 1880-3, 1955 revision by r. G. Blanchard, Topographic Engineer. Revision of 1972 by the staff of the Bureau of Geology and Topography.
dct_publisher_sm: Trenton, N.J. : New Jersey Geological Survey, 1972.
